SIMPLE: multipolar
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Multipolar
<hw>Mul`ti*po"lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Multi-</ets> + <ets>polar</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having many poles; in <fld>Anat.</fld>, designating specif. a nerve
cell which has several dendrites.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>Having, or pertaining to, many
poles, as a field magnet or armature of a dynamo, or a dynamo having
such a field magnet or (sometimes) armature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Multipotent</ent>⟦br⟧
